
[1]encourage

   ENCOUR'AGE, v.t. enkur'rage. To give courage to; to give or increase
   confidence of success; to inspire with courage, spirit, or strength of
   mind; to embolden; to animate; to incite; to inspirit.

   But charge Joshua, and encourage him. Deut. 3.
